The article announces the details of the upcoming White House Easter Egg Roll, which is a tradition that dates back to 1878. The event will take place on April 22, 2019, on the South Lawn of the White House. Families with children aged 13 and younger are invited to join the President, First Lady, White House staff, and their families for a day of festivities. 

Tickets for the Easter Egg Roll can be requested through an online lottery, which will open on February 28, 2019, and close on March 4, 2019. Winners will be notified by email on March 14, 2019. Tickets are free and not for sale or resale. 

Volunteer opportunities for the Egg Roll are also available. Interested individuals can submit an application online, with the deadline being March 7, 2019. Applicants will be notified by March 15, 2019.

Additionally, this year's official White House Easter Egg Roll commemorative eggs will be available to the general public. More information will be provided on the lottery's website.